            <h3 id="focus-management" class="doc-h3">Focus Management</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Visible focus indicator:</strong> All focusable elements (search input, group headers, nav items) must display a visible focus ring that meets WCAG 2.4.7.</li>
              <li><strong>Search bar focus:</strong> The search input receives a 2px blue border (<code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">#006AFF</code>) plus a 3px shadow ring when focused.</li>
              <li><strong>Group header focus:</strong> Headers are <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;button&gt;</code> elements and receive default browser focus styles plus custom outline styling.</li>
              <li><strong>Active item focus:</strong> When navigating with keyboard, the active item retains its accent background while also showing the focus indicator.</li>
            </ul>
